<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-13"><hi rend="italic">December 13,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root informs Mr. Rockhill that he has agreed with the Chinese
                            minister to reduce the Lienchou final indemnity to $25,000 gold, and
                            authorizes him to close, with this modification, the agreement set forth
                            in his No. 381.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>